Malaysia Stocks: AirAsia, Fajarbaru, Fotronics, Sunway Holdings

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-03-07T09:18:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/malaysia-stocks-airasia-fajarbaru-fotronics-sunway-holdings.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Malaysia trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 5 p.m. close in  Kuala
Lumpur .  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index fell 6.87, or 0.4
percent, to 1,515.74, its first decline in three days.  Airline stocks:  AirAsia Bhd. (AIRA)  , Southeast Asiaâ€™s
biggest budget carrier, and  Malaysian Airline System Bhd. (MAS)  fell
on concern fuel costs will increase as oil climbed to a 29-month
high. AirAsia slid 1.6 percent to 2.48 ringgit, the steepest
drop since March 2. Malaysian Airline fell 3.2 percent to 1.81
ringgit.    Fajarbaru Builder Group Bhd. (FBC)  , a builder, climbed
1.9 percent to 1.07 ringgit, its highest close since Feb. 25.
The company said it won two civil works contracts worth 150.1
million ringgit, according to an exchange filing.  Fotronics Corp. (FOT MK), an electronic components
manufacturer, slid 33 percent to 1 sen. The company announced a
restructuring plan under which it would transfer its listing
status to a new company called Urus Jaring Sdn. Fotronics
stockholders would receive one share in the new company for
every 10 existing shares held, it said in a statement.    Sunway Holdings Bhd. (SGW)  , a construction and property
group, advanced 0.9 percent to 2.20 ringgit, the lowest close
since Feb. 21. Sunway won a 258 million ringgit contract to help
construct part of the Legoland Malaysia Theme Park in southern
Johor state, according to a company statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
